1️⃣ Alpha/Beta and Theta/Beta Ratio Stress Paper

📄 EEG stress analysis on alpha/beta ratio and theta/beta ratio (paper)

Key points from the paper:

Stress detection uses Alpha/Beta ratio and Theta/Beta ratio.

EEG signals are converted to frequency features using FFT and Power Spectral Density (PSD).

These ratios change significantly when a person is stressed.

Important finding:

Lower Alpha/Beta ratio → higher stress

Lower Theta/Beta ratio → higher stress

This is one of the most commonly cited metrics for EEG stress detection.

